From: Anirudh Venkataramanan <anirudh.venkataramanan@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 2 Aug 2019 01:25:25 -0700
Subject: ice: Fix EMP reset handling
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc1
Git-commit: 03af840650bb4a1cfa95ea93493d04b679ab5f5c
References: jsc#SLE-7926

ice_reset_subtask needs to handle EMP resets as well, as EMP resets
can be triggered by the firmware. This patch adds the logic to do
this.

Signed-off-by: Anirudh Venkataramanan <anirudh.venkataramanan@intel.com>
Tested-by: Andrew Bowers <andrewx.bowers@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_main.c
@@ -567,6 +567,8 @@ static void ice_reset_subtask(struct ice
 			reset_type = ICE_RESET_CORER;
 		if (test_and_clear_bit(__ICE_GLOBR_RECV, pf->state))
 			reset_type = ICE_RESET_GLOBR;
+		if (test_and_clear_bit(__ICE_EMPR_RECV, pf->state))
+			reset_type = ICE_RESET_EMPR;
 		/* return if no valid reset type requested */
 		if (reset_type == ICE_RESET_INVAL)
 			return;
